.TH "vic_register" 9 "vic_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vic_register \- Register a VIC.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vic_register
.BI "(void __iomem *base "  ","
.BI "unsigned int parent_irq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int irq "  ","
.BI "u32 valid_sources "  ","
.BI "u32 resume_sources "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
The base address of the VIC.
.IP "parent_irq" 12
The parent IRQ if cascaded, else 0.
.IP "irq" 12
The base IRQ for the VIC.
.IP "valid_sources" 12
bitmask of valid interrupts
.IP "resume_sources" 12
bitmask of interrupts allowed for resume sources.
.IP "node" 12
The device tree node associated with the VIC.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register the VIC with the system device tree so that it can be notified
of suspend and resume requests and ensure that the correct actions are
taken to re-instate the settings on resume.

This also configures the IRQ domain for the VIC.
